        // "exhibit_explain_1" : "'The Origin of All Beginnings' is a media art exhibition on Nodeul Island, where the lights of the city and the waters of the Hangang River come together.\n\nThrough the dynamic works of two media artists, the exhibition explores moments of origin and creation while highlighting the artistic charm of Nodeul Island and the new possibilities of the Hangang River.",
        // "exhibit_explain_name_2" : "Moment Seoul",
        // "exhibit_explain_2" : "'Moment Seoul' highlights one of Seoul's core values: a compassionate city that walks alongside the vulnerable.\nThrough Spring Message of Support from Seoul, it delivers messages of encouragement to citizens facing new beginnings, while Haechi’s Seoul Journey follows a journey from Nodeul Island to the skies above Seoul, set against the scenery of Nodeul Island and the Hangang River.",
        // "exhibit_explain_name_3" : "Hangang Nature",
        // "exhibit_explain_3" : "'Hangang Nature' represents Seoul's vision of 'Charm', presenting a media-art nature archive of the living ecology of Nodeul Island and the Hangang River.\n\nThrough an omnibus animation featuring the \"Maengkkongi\" the boreal digging frog, as its main character, the work follows a journey in search of a new home, conveying the island's ecology, seasonal changes, and the diverse landscapes of Seoul and the Hangang River.",
        
        "exhibit_2_intro_title" : "Exhibition Introduction",        
        "exhibit_2_introduce_name" : "2nd Exhibition 07.01.-09.19.",
        "exhibit_2_introduce" : "Seoullo Media Canvas' second exhibition in 2026 welcomes visitors with diverse views of the city, nature, and young creators amid the ripe summer scenery. The exhibition will consist of the Nature Project and the University Cooperation Exhibition, which will showcase the changing landscape of the city, the cycle of nature, and the new generation's sense of looking at it through media art.",
        // "exhibit_2_introduce_sub" : "",
        "exhibit_2_explain_name_1" : "The University Collaboration Exhibition",
        "exhibit_2_explain_1" : "The University Cooperation Exhibition introduces the fresh imagination and experimental gaze of university students who will lead the field of media art in the future. Works that interpret Seoul's daily and seasonal senses, tradition and modernity, and individual memories and emotions in various ways meet with citizens through public media platforms and create a new place of empathy.",
        "exhibit_2_explain_name_2" : "Nature Project Exhibition",
        "exhibit_2_explain_2" : "The Nature Project Exhibition explores the vitality, the passage of time, and the value of recovery and circulation that nature possesses. Works dealing with changes in the four seasons, restoration of ecosystems, records of nature in everyday life, and connectivity from microscopic life to the great universe offer various perspectives on nature and give viewers time to think.",
